15 Section 3. KRS 189A.340 is amended to read as follows:
16 (1) (a) If a person's license is suspended pursuant to this chapter and the initial
17 suspension was for a violation of KRS 189A.010(1)(a), (b), (e), or (f), the sole
18 license the person shall be eligible for is an ignition interlock license pursuant
19 to this section.
20 (b) If a person's license is suspended pursuant to this chapter and the initial
21 suspension was for a violation of KRS 189A.010(1)(c) or (d), the person shall
22 be eligible for an ignition interlock license pursuant to this section and may be
23 eligible for a hardship license pursuant to KRS 189A.410.
24 (2) (a) A person may apply for an ignition interlock license anytime, including after
25 receiving the notices under KRS 189A.105 or after his or her license has been
26 suspended pursuant to this chapter.
27 (b) If at the time the person applies for an ignition interlock license, the person's
